  "market_context": "ETH on Monday consolidated through Asia and London sessions, then manipulated lower into the New York open. The analyst frames this as an accumulation-manipulation sequence on the daily, anticipating distribution higher into the previous day high as the draw on liquidity.",
  "key_observation": "Asia/London accumulation followed by NY-open manipulation lower sets up an AMD long, with previous day high serving as the distribution target and a 5-minute fair value gap providing the entry trigger.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: On the daily/HTF, identify consolidation through Asia and London sessions as the accumulation phase.",
    "Step 2: Note the manipulation leg down into the New York open, completing the A-M portion of AMD.",
    "Step 3: Set the previous day high as the distribution target and draw on liquidity.",
    "Step 4: Drop to lower time frames to find an entry; consider a retest of the deviation per the box setup.",
    "Step 5: On the 5-minute chart, identify a fair value gap formed during the displacement higher.",
    "Step 6: Enter long at the 5-minute FVG with stop below the manipulation low, targeting the previous day high.",
    "Step 7: Confirm trade qualifies with approximately 2R risk-to-reward."
  ],
  "outcome": "Trade played out: price reached slightly lower into the range deviation, rejected off the new week opening gap consequent encroachment, then expanded higher into the previous day high, completing the AMD distribution.",
  "lessons": "Top-down analysis works: establish AMD bias on the higher time frame using session structure, then drop to the 5-minute for a fair value gap entry. Framing the previous day high as the draw on liquidity gives a clear target and a clean 2R setup.",
